# Normalize line endings to LF on checkout for all text files so shell scripts,
# Python, and JS sources are byte-identical across Linux, macOS, and Windows.
#
# Without this, git for Windows (core.autocrlf=true by default) checks out text
# files with CRLF line endings. Sourcing a CRLF claudecfg/hooks/lib.sh in bash
# appends a stray \r to string literals and case patterns, corrupting the
# footer-contract / message-recognition / command_class functions and breaking
# the pytest suite that sources lib.sh (test_message_mentions, test_high_bugs,
# test_medium_bugs, test_hook_effective_roles, test_concrete_outcome_recognition).
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect binary files (NUL bytes) and leave them alone;
# `eol=lf` forces LF on both checkin and checkout, overriding autocrlf.
* text=auto eol=lf